While most politicians are arguing over how to reopen the economy, only Sessions is addressing the impact legal immigration has on jobs.
In addition to the Chinese virus, two more pandemics will be top issues: job loss and legal immigration.
Support for an immigration moratorium is rising among conservative leaders and the American people as a whole.
Tom Cotton, R-Ark., David Perdue, R-Ga., and Josh Hawley, R-Mo., who all support the RAISE Act, which cuts legal immigration.
Come 2021, whoever the next Alabama senator is, they should be voting on an immigration moratorium bill if one has not already passed.